        "institution": {
            "title": "A living institution for over six centuries",
            "p1": "Founded in 1394 by King Ncharé Yen, the Bamoun Kingdom instituted the NGUON as a community governance mechanism, for social regulation and celebration of the Kingdom's founding values.",
            "p2": "Born from a quest for land, unity and cohesion, the Bamoun Kingdom structured itself around principles of symbiosis, balance and collective responsibility, symbolized by the beetle, emblem of the NGUON.",
            "p3": "Banned between 1924 and 1960 by the colonial administration, the NGUON was rehabilitated after Cameroon's independence, then institutionalized in 1992 as the Great Traditional, Cultural and Economic Days of the Bamoun people."
        },
        "recognition": {
            "title": "A recognized heritage",
